.TH "drm_gem_cma_create_with_handle" 9 "drm_gem_cma_create_with_handle" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drm_gem_cma_create_with_handle \- allocate an object with the given size and return a GEM handle to it
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct drm_gem_cma_object *" drm_gem_cma_create_with_handle
.BI "(struct drm_file *file_priv "  ","
.BI "struct drm_device *drm "  ","
.BI "size_t size "  ","
.BI "uint32_t *handle "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "file_priv" 12
DRM file-private structure to register the handle for
.IP "drm" 12
DRM device
.IP "size" 12
size of the object to allocate
.IP "handle" 12
return location for the GEM handle
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function creates a CMA GEM object, allocating a physically contiguous
chunk of memory as backing store. The GEM object is then added to the list
of object associated with the given file and a handle to it is returned.
.SH "RETURN"
A struct drm_gem_cma_object * on success or an \fBERR_PTR\fP-encoded negative
error code on failure.
